org.openimaj.data.dataset

Class ListBackedDataset<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openimaj.data.dataset.ListBackedDataset<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of items in the dataset
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<T>, Collection<T>, List<T>, Dataset<T>, ListDataset<T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Corel5kDataset, FDDBDataset

    public class ListBackedDataset<T>
extends Object
implements ListDataset<T>
    A ListBackedDataset is a Dataset backed by an ordered list of items. For convenience, the dataset is itself presented as as list.
    Author:
    Jonathon Hare (jsh2@ecs.soton.ac.uk)

      • ListBackedDataset

        public ListBackedDataset(Iterable<T> iterator)
        Construct by consuming the contents of the given iterator into the backing list.

        Obviously this method could cause problems if the number of items in the iterator is very large, as memory could be exhausted. Care should be taken.

        Parameters:
        iterator - the data to read
